texts.text: >Elohim continues to push the Liberators to their limit.

There is no use!
Give up!
*Shriek*
*Scream*
>Your demons disappear.
Dammit, they're gone...!

This is bad.
We don't have much left in the tank.
Yo, we don't even know what kind of trials are waitin' for us after this.
At this rate, we're gonna be down for the count even if we do get outta here...
If only we had a way of one-shotting this guy...

Alright...
You guys go on without me.
I'll deal with Elohim myself.
Say what?!
What are you saying, Vince?! Are you insane?!
Yeah!
The second trial's about defeating Elohim.
Going on ahead without actually doing that...
Sabaoth said to meet it on the roof, right?
It didn't say anything about going together or having to win first.
No strings as far as I can see.
I hate to say it, but he might be right...
All's fair in love and war, right?
I'm still gonna be dealing with this trial, so they shouldn't be allowed to complain.
Vince...
Yo, Vince, this is Elohim we're talkin' about.
It ain't goin' down that easily...
That's the point.
Imagine if we get wiped here.
There won't be anyone left to go up to the roof and it'll be game over for our world.
I don't care what actually happens to this piece-of-shit world.
But you guys still want to do something about it, right?
Look, I can't count how many Elohim I beat in that parallel world.
I know just how much it sucks to fight this thing.
But...!
Okay.
We're on the same side, aren't we?
Just trust me on this.
That's it, [sys user_name].
It's nice knowing that you don't like to drag your feet.
Let's go, everyone.
Honey...

Vince is strong!
He'll be fine!
Go kick its butt!

You know I will.
See, she gets it.
Aight...
We'll keep goin'.
Yo, just promise to meet us up there when you're done.
That's an order.
Good luck, Vince.
I should say this just in case.
Don't be an idiot by sacrificing yourself or anything. I hate it when people do that.
Hah! Thanks, but I'm not asking for any sympathy.
I don't plan on becoming an upstanding citizen anytime soon.
>The Liberators all nod in agreement and head off running.
>Their footsteps echo loudly as they climb back up the stairs.
Ah, they have chosen to flee from their trial.
Wrong.
They left because I can handle you all on my own.
You believe you can win?
Fool. You have but little strength left to fight...
But so be it.
Allow me to lay your soul to rest by facilitating its "end".
This will be farewell.
*Roar*
>Light begins to gather upon Elohim and its surroundings.
>It is attempting to produce a massive amount of energy!
Damn, you've become a lot stronger. I'll give you that...
What happened to the little spirit that couldn't do anything without my help?
You arrogant, ungrateful pest...!
There is no saving you.
Those who defy God shall face judgment...!
>Elohim produces an enormous ball of light!
>And then...

Devil Download!
Go get it!
What?!
*Roar*
>Elohim is hit!

You snuck behind me...?
But I am a Godly spirit...?
Did you not run with your friends, Homunculus?
Why are you here?
Hah! You're pretty stupid for a Godly being.

Honey's my partner.
There's no way she would've left me behind.
He kept you busy while I snuck around behind you!
Just like real bad guys, right, Vince?
Yeah! Get rid of your opponents while wasting as little energy as possible!
Heathens...
I've been waiting to kick your ass like this for a while now, Elohim.
You're gonna regret picking a fight with us!
So let's dance!
*Roar*
>The remaining Liberators make their way up the stairs.

*Pant*
Yo, finally, the roof!
But it's night already. Also, where's Sabaoth?
Humans, you have done well to make it this far.
But I see that not all of you are present.
Or did you sacrifice one of your own in the name of victory...?
No way! Yo, we left him because we believe in him.
Vince and Honey will be here soon. You'll see!
I do not care either way.
It is academic at this point.
Now, for your final trial...
I, Sabaoth, the Lord of the Armies...
I stand before thee as one who commands heaven and Earth, as one who is a part of God himself.
Defeat me if you can, Liberators!
